This paper discusses the use of online learning algorithms for designing model predictive control (MPC) algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which is focused on the development and analysis of control systems. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper presents experiments on simulated and real-world driving tasks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a new algorithm, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
